This will include openposix_testsuite from LTP.

The POSIX Test Suite is an open source test suite with the goal of
performing conformance, functional, and stress testing of the IEEE
1003.1-2001 System Interfaces specification in a manner that is
agnostic to any given implementation.

NOTE:
[] When editing this task you will need the following rpm 
   installed on your local system, in order to commit to GIT 
   and update the Beaker task rpm:
     Linux Test Project - include
     https://beaker.engineering.redhat.com/tasks/4941

There is number of known issues, which are excluded from testing on RHEL.
Linux (including RHEL) is not 100% compliant with open posix.
